F7rsV2I1rHs.title: "JIANG RONG QIAO BAGUA 8 PALMS"
F7rsV2I1rHs.description:
BaGua student Malcom training the 8 palm change of Jiang Rong Qiao BaGuaZhang.Learn BaGuaZhang for Fitness , Combat, Mobility & Longevity. BaGuaZhang Classes now forming for Seniors on the upper west side of Harlem. Private Classes N' Group Classes call: 646 895-9262 for more information.
Now available NEW Jiang Rong Qiao BaGuaZhang instructional DVD which contains the 8 palms, Standing Chi Kung and combat applications of the system:
http://www.lulu.com/product/dvd/jiang-rong-qiao-baguazhang/4200661?productTrackingContext=search_results/search_shelf/center/3


Biography of Jiang Rong Qiao:

In 1926, Jiang Rong Qiao began teaching kung fu in Nanjing. Jiang was instrumental in developing sets that combined Bagua, Xingyi, and Taijiquan. This includes a Tajiquan set known as Taiji Zhang Quan (or Tai Chi Palm and Fist), which is based on sequences from Jiang's Bagua and Xingyi, as well as the Old Chen Style Tai Chi Chuan. Some students of Jiang Rong Qiao point to these combined forms as a legacy of his teacher Zhang Zhaodong. The practice of internal style Chinese martial arts (Baguazhang, Xingyiquan and Taijiquan and a variety of minor styles) has been called Neijia kung fu. Because Jiang Rong Qiao taught Baguazhang along with Xingyiquan (and taught Taiji Zhang Quan as an advanced form), it is difficult to categorize the practice he taught as anything other than Neijia kung fu.

Jiang had an accident and went blind. Jiang's adopted daughter, Zou Shu Xian, taught classes and helped produce his most famous book, Bagua Palms Practice Method. This was the first Baguazhang book published in China after the 1949 revolution. This book greatly enhanced Jiang's reputation as one of the most famous Chinese Internal style Martial Artists of his generation. Jiang Rong Qiao died at the age of 84. Several of his closest students were: Sha Guo Zhen, Zou Shu Xian, Ji Yuan Song, and Yang Bang Tai.

tePQy2eMRg0.title: Mozart / Julius Baker, 1962: Andante For Flute and Orchestra in G, K. 315 - Antonio Janigro, cond.
tePQy2eMRg0.description:
From the LP shown above, issued in 1966 on the Vanguard label.  Julius Baker, soloist.  The late Italian cellist Antonio Janigro leads I Solisti de Zagreb.


Джулиус Бейкер (англ. Julius Baker; 23 сентября 1915, Кливленд — 8 августа 2003) — американский флейтист.  Учился в Кёртисовском институте у Уильяма Кинкейда, занимался также у Марселя Табюто. После окончания института в 1937 г. вернулся в Кливленд, до 1941 г. играл в Кливлендском оркестре. В 1941—1943 гг. был первой флейтой Питсбургского симфонического оркестра, затем переехал в Нью-Йорк и выступал в составе Колумбийского симфонического оркестра — коллектива, собранного из музыкантов различных оркестров для аудизаписей фирмы Columbia Records. В 1951—1953 гг. в Чикагском симфоническом оркестре, затем на протяжении почти 30 лет в Нью-Йоркском филармоническом оркестре.
"David Hertzberg"

When Kavya (Kaajal Aggarwal) comes to Sawantwadi, from Goa to visit her grandparents on a vacation she is charmed by Bajirao's bold and courageous demeanor.
